com.yworks.yfiles.view.input

Class MoveLabelInputMode

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.yworks.yfiles.view.input.MoveInputMode
      • com.yworks.yfiles.view.input.MoveLabelInputMode
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IInputMode

    public class MoveLabelInputMode
extends MoveInputMode
    An IInputMode that can be used to drag a ILabel in a GraphControl.

    This implementation shows the possible candidate positions for a given label and allows the user to drag the label to one of these positions.

    • Method Detail

      • createLabelHitTestable

        protected IHitTestable createLabelHitTestable()
        Creates the hit testable that will be used to determine whether this mode may be activated.

        This implementation returns an instance that delegates to isValidLabelHit(IInputModeContext, PointD).

        Returns:
        A hit testable.

      • createLabelPositionHandler

        protected IPositionHandler createLabelPositionHandler(ILabel label)
        Creates the position handler for the given label used in isValidLabelHit(IInputModeContext, PointD).

        First, this implementation checks for a position handler in the label's lookup. If this fails, it creates a new label position handler for the given label.

        Parameters:
        label - The label to create a position handler for.
        Returns:
        A position handler for the given label.

      • getHitLabel

        protected ILabel getHitLabel(IInputModeContext context,
                             PointD location)
        Looks for a label that has been hit at the specified position.

        This implementation checks the GraphSelection to see if there is exactly one selected label. This label is returned if it is hit by the mouse and shouldMove(IInputModeContext, ILabel) returns true. Otherwise, null is returned.

        Parameters:
        context - The context for the hit test.
        location - The coordinates for the hit test.
        Returns:
        The label hit at the given location or null.
        See Also:
        isValidLabelHit(IInputModeContext, PointD), shouldMove(IInputModeContext, ILabel)

      • getMovedLabel

        public final ILabel getMovedLabel()
        Gets the label that is currently moved or null if there is no such label.

        The value of this property is not null only if this mode is currently active and performs a move operation, that is between the DragStarting and the DragFinished event handlers.

        Returns:
        The MovedLabel.

      • isUsingLabelModelParameterFinderEnabled

        public final boolean isUsingLabelModelParameterFinderEnabled()
        Gets a value indicating whether or not using the ILabelModelParameterFinder to assign new label model parameters is allowed.

        The default is true

        This property has no effect if an IPositionHandler is available in the label's lookup.

        Returns:
        The UsingLabelModelParameterFinderEnabled.
        See Also:
        createLabelPositionHandler(ILabel), setUsingLabelModelParameterFinderEnabled(boolean)

      • isValidLabelHit

        protected boolean isValidLabelHit(IInputModeContext context,
                                  PointD location)
        Determines whether or not a valid label has been hit at the specified position.

        This implementation calls getHitLabel(IInputModeContext, PointD) to find the label at the specified location. If a label is hit, the IPositionHandler is created by createLabelPositionHandler(ILabel).

        Parameters:
        context - The context for the hit test.
        location - The coordinates for the hit test.
        Returns:
        true if a valid label is hit and the label moving should be started here. Otherwise, false.

      • shouldMove

        protected boolean shouldMove(IInputModeContext context,
                             ILabel label)
        Determines whether or not a label is allowed to be moved.

        This implementation returns false if the parent input mode forbids moving the label. Overriding implementations should query this implementation as base if this feature is desired.

        Parameters:
        context - The context.
        label - The label to be checked.
        Returns:
        true if the label is allowed to move.
        See Also:
        getHitLabel(IInputModeContext, PointD)
